Name: Short and Sweet
Description: Songs that are under 2 minutes in runtime

Name: Songs that Remind You of Home
Description: Fairly self explanatory. What's harder is whether the goal is for it to remind everyone of home or just be a song that reminds you of home and hope others like it. Probably the latter.

Name: Songs not in English
Description: Let's get some other languages in here. I don't want to understand a word in the songs sent.

Name: First Dance Songs
Description: An opportunity to convince Hannah and Grant that your song clearly should be the song for their first dance

Name: Gender-Swapped Covers
Description: Women covering men. Men covering women. These covers change up the vibe

Name: Songs on Your First iPod
Description: These are the songs you pulled off of LimeWire in the mid thousands. Or I suppose you could've acquired them legally.

Name: Storytelling Songs
Description: These are songs that tell a story in the third person. Maybe a ballad or some solid folklore in there.

Name: Best Instrument Solo
Description: We're looking for the best solo in a song where the rest of the band steps back and lets one instrument take the lead and show off how ridiculously talented people are at making music.

Name: My Cup of Tea
Description: This is about having songs that you love but maybe not everyone does. Bring out your hot takes, your ugly ducklings, and your last picks. Let's see if you can convince people to give a strange song a chance.

Name: Niche Pulls
Description: Submit a song from a mostly unknown artist. (To help with line drawing we are looking for under 250k monthly listeners on spotify.) Who do you know that no one else does?

Name: Pre-Pearl Harbor Music (Dec. 7, 1941)
Description: Harken back to a time when the United States really wanted to not get involved in other countries conflicts. What oldies do you think not get the credit they deserve?

Name: Your Song of the Summer
Description: August, June, and July have all passed us by. Look back on the summer of 2025 and share which song got you through the dog days of these hot summer months.
